President Muhammadu Buhari proceeded to London, the United Kingdom, on Tuesday, for a routine medical check-up.
The President met with Security Chiefs first in the morning, after which he embarked on the journey.
President Buhari is due back in the country in the second week of April 2021.
Many Nigerians have expressed concerns that the president departed the country on medical trip less than one week he took the corona vaccine jab. Some other construe the president’s medical trip to the UK as epitomizing his failure to develop the health system in Nigeria, just like the preceding presidents.
 
